Ajai Singh "Sonny" Mehta is a publisher and editor-in-chief of Alfred A Knopf who moved in with Douglas Adams in order to make sure Adams finished his book, So Long, and Thanks for All the Fish.

Mehta appears in the largely fictional world of Lunar Park, in which Bret Easton Ellis mixes fact and fiction in a pseudo-memoir. Mehta also gets a namecheck in the musical, "The Last Five Years." External links 
